text: Ecyrus arcuatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Charles Joseph Gahan in 1892. It is known from Mexico, Honduras, Guatemala, and United States.BioLib.cz - Ecyrus arcuatus. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. ==References== Category:Pogonocherini Category:Beetles described in 1892
